Package com.tknkla.rj

Interface ExecutionStrategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ForkJoinPoolExecutionStrategy
    public interface ExecutionStrategy
    Parallel execution strategy.

    Parallelization in RJ is based on parallel execution of divide-and-conquer patterns.

    This interface defines an execution pattern which attempts to minimize synchronization between threads. Do note that the current interface is not final (semantic versioning applies only partially) and thus custom implementations may not be directly compatible with future versions.

    For an example of usage, see source code of RJ.execute(int, int, int, java.util.function.IntUnaryOperator, IntBinaryOperator).

    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Timo Santasalo
    See Also:
    RJ.setExecutor(ExecutionStrategy)

      • LOCAL

        static final ExecutionStrategy LOCAL
        Default non-parallel execution strategy.

        fork(int) always returns false and every other method throws an IllegalStateException.

        Since:
        1.0.0

      • PARALLEL

        static final ExecutionStrategy PARALLEL
        Default parallel execution strategy based on ForkJoinPool.commonPool() (work size is 4).

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        void execute​(Consumer<Runnable> fn)
        Executes a task, blocking until the execution is complete.

        fork(int) must be queried before invoking this method.

        The task must execute the provided Consumer after it is complete.

        If this method is called from inside the task, the implementation must ensure that blocking doesn't deadlock.

        The default implementation delegates to execute(Consumer).

        Parameters:
        fn - Task.

      • fork

        boolean fork​(int taskSize)
        Checks whether a work of given size should be split and queued instead of being executed by a non-parallel algorithm.

        This method must be invoked before every execute and should be invoked before every queue.

        If task size is less than or equal to one, always returns false.

        Parameters:
        taskSize - Size of the work to be parallelized.
        Returns:
        True, if work can be parallelized.

      • create

        static ExecutionStrategy create​(int concurrency,
                                int workSize)
        Creates an execution strategy.

        If concurrency is zero, LOCAL is returned; otherwise an instance of ForkJoinPoolExecutionStrategy is created with an associated pool which can be accessed through ForkJoinPoolExecutionStrategy.getPool()

        Parameters:
        concurrency - Concurrency number (base-2 logarithm of number of threads).
        workSize - Minimal work size
        Returns:
        An execution strategy.
